\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Personnel security is the County's first defensive layer against insider risk and unauthorized disclosure of sensitive information.
 This policy implements federal personnel security requirements for Criminal Justice Information (CJI) access while establishing County-wide screening standards for all access to County IT resources.
 Per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 §6.11,
 the IT Director holds the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) designation by policy mandate.
 This policy cites the IT Director (as LASO) when the CJIS liaison function is specifically invoked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Position Risk and Access Classification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall assign each position an access classification (General,
 Privileged,
 or CJI).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Classification Definitions
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General
\series default
:
 Standard user access to County IT resources that are not designated as CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged
\series default
:
 Elevated permissions capable of altering system configurations or security controls,
 corresponding to Role Tiers L3 through L5 as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Workforce Roles,
 Responsibilities,
 and Competency Framework) §6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI
\series default
:
 Any position with potential unescorted access to unencrypted CJI.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Screening Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Clearance,
 No Access
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall not provision access until screening and adjudication are complete for the applicable classification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General Access
\series default
:
 Human Resources shall complete County-required identity verification and background screening prior to the IT Director provisioning access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Access
\series default
:
 Human Resources shall coordinate the submission of state-of-residency and national fingerprint-based record checks through an FBI-approved authority prior to the IT Director provisioning access.
 Final adjudication of CJI Access eligibility shall follow CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3 as applied in Section 6.3.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 "Pending" or temporary access to CJI environments is prohibited.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 CJI Adjudication Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Felony Convictions
\series default
:
 If a felony conviction of any kind exists,
 the IT Director shall deny CJI access.
 The requesting agency may request a review by the CSO in extenuating circumstances where the severity of the offense and the time that has passed would support a possible variance,
 per CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3(a)(3)(a).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Misdemeanors
\series default
:
 Where the CSO has formally delegated misdemeanor adjudication authority to the IT Director per CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3(a)(3)(b),
 the IT Director may grant CJI access if the offense does not meet the disqualification criteria established by the CSO.
 Absent formal written delegation,
 the IT Director shall refer the matter to the CSO for determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fugitive Status or Unresolved Arrest
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall deny CJI access to any individual with an active warrant.
 For individuals with an arrest history without conviction,
 where the CSO has formally delegated review authority to the IT Director per CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3(a)(4),
 the IT Director may grant or continue access based on the review outcome.
 Absent formal written delegation,
 the IT Director shall refer the matter to the CSO for determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorized CJI Access List
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall maintain a current record of all personnel authorized for unescorted access to unencrypted CJI,
 per CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3(a)(7).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall provide the record to the CSO or the CSO's designee upon request.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CSO Notification
\series default
:
 The IT Director (as LASO) shall notify the CSO in writing of any denial of CJI access,
 any suspected violation of CJIS Security Policy,
 and any continued-access determination arising under Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Continued Access Review
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Notification Trigger
\series default
:
 Upon receipt from Human Resources of a notification of a court or law-enforcement action that may affect an individual's fitness for continued CJI access,
 the IT Director shall review continued CJI access in accordance with CJIS Security Policy v6.0 PS-3(a)(5).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Self-Reporting Non-Compliance
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall suspend access within thirty (30) minutes of determining that an individual failed to self-report a court or law-enforcement action within the twenty-four (24) hour window established in Section 3.
 For CJI Access,
 final access determination shall follow the adjudication process defined in Section 6.3.
\end_layout

