\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Exit Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exit Interview — County Employees and Appointed Personnel
\series default
:
 Human Resources shall conduct an exit interview covering non-disclosure obligations for Criminal Justice Information (CJI) and Personally Identifiable Information (PII) under NRS 239B for every separating County employee or appointed official who held logical or physical access to County IT resources.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exception
\series default
:
 Where the separating individual is unavailable (e.g.,
 job abandonment,
 sudden incapacitation,
 or refusal to participate),
 Human Resources shall execute alternate separation handling consisting of documented reason for the missed interview and a written non-disclosure reminder delivered to the individual's last known address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 Credential recovery and asset recovery obligations under this section shall remain in force regardless of whether an exit interview is conducted.
\end_layout

